nts1.n: THE EARLY BIRD SHOW W/ EDDIE FICTION
nts1.d: Introducing The Early Bird Show - our radio offering for morning people, hosted by Maria Somerville (Mondays and Tuesdays), Spirit Blue (Wednesdays and Thursdays) and Jack Rollo (Fridays). Weekday mornings, 7-9am.

nts1.n: THE NTS BREAKFAST SHOW W/ SMERZ
nts1.d: Everyone's favourite Norwegian duo close out a bumper year with a special cover edition of the NTS Breakfast Show.
Let NTS brighten up your lunchtime hours.

nts1.n: GOD'S WAITING ROOM W/ DAVID HOLMES
nts1.d: God's Waiting Room: a round-about selection of the cinematic, library music, rock 'n' roll, psych, experimental, unclassifiable and independent. From the mind of DJ, producer and creator of original soundtracks, David Holmes.
Dive into Donna Leake's ever developing taste, drawing sounds from all over the globe and all over the clock including jazz, reggae and psych.

nts1.n: A Scene In Between w/ Samuel Knee - US acid soaked folk garage punk melancholia 1965-68
nts1.d: Sam Knee navigates and curates lost underground countercultural sounds with deep dives into specific sub-scenes, regions, years, labels of the near mythical 80’s post punk DIY indie guitar era and beyond, back to its 60s basement punk genesis.
Welcome to Club Coco: a place where globe-trotting vinyl hunter Coco María shares her joyous discoveries - jazz, fusion, international pop, vintage latin music of all flavours…
Ziggy Devriendt is the DJ behind Nosedrip. Tune in once a month for an expert selection of any or all of the following: new age, new wave, French psych, minimal synth, post-punk and a whole lot else…

Artist, producer, label owner and DJ Lee Gamble bringing an oneiric bi-monthly show of current sound and music from his hallucinated musical continuum. Expect anything from Drill to Dream pop, Conceptual Sound and Jazz to bleached out rave memories..

nts1.n: FRACTAL MEAT ON A SPONGY BONE

nts2.d: High Jazz* is an independent record label specializing in 70s & 80s soul, jazz & funk. ill Dubio takes the reigns for the monthly High Jazz* show rustling up an hour of choice selections on a Wednesday.

Carolina Soul is a record seller based in Durham, NC, USA. They specialize in rare and classic soul, boogie, gospel and modern obscure tracks from the Carolinas and beyond, mixed with all-time bangers and ballads.

nts2.n: THE WONDER CABINET w/ Ramsy Kattan, Joseph Schiano Di Lombo, Alabaster DePlume and Jude
nts2.d:
Sounds and recordings from resident artists at the Wonder Cabinet space in Cremisan Valley, Bethlehem.
From the host: "Live recordings from Wonder Cabinet's concerts and open sessions in December 2025. in Bethlehem, Palestine."
Broken club, dubbed out sounds, experimental electronics and atonal drifts: Gio’s monthly broadcasts are high contrast assemblages that move at a slow pace.
Melbourne based producer YL HOOI share an hour of dub, electronics, postpunk and more every month…

Monthly mixes and "Bad behaviour" from the crew behind Berlin's acclaimed Mala Junta parties. Expect throwback trance, souped up '90s basslines and party music of a high tempo flavour.
From the host: "Jen Cardini delivers the celebration needed to close the year! A bassy, electro fever dream blasting with percussive sensuality"

nts2.n: HIT A LICK RADIO w/ DJ Finnahitalick
nts2.d: Chester, PA’s DJ FINNAHITALICK (Blackwealth in the club) is a seasoned sound archivist of Underground Hip-hop. Starting Hit A Lick Radio in 2016, DJ FINNAHITALICK explores rap’s extensive subgenres and regional epicenters, ranging from DMV crank and Atlanta Plugg to Milwaukee low-end, Michigan punch-rap and beyond. His fast-paced mixes encapsulate Underground Hip-hop’s diverse landscape, and are not for the weak-hearted.
Native Sound System join us once a month, breaking the latest sounds from Lagos
Regular hours from the D.C. archivists and record label, famed for uncovering + documenting folk and global traditional music.
Head of Grimy Edits, Zernell Gillie's style can range from the heart of disco to the soul of Chicago house - he heads up a 2 hour slot once a month from our LA studio.
A mix of seasonal, frosty compositions from early sacred vocal works through choral, orchestral, and piano repertoire, spanning medieval, romantic, and 20th-century composition.

subtle.d: Saraphim (aka RNS & RDubz) are two Essex based Producer/DJ’s currently focused on Dubstep & the 140 spectrum, mixing ethnical and grime influences into their music. You can expect anything from deep and melodic meditative vibes to high energy driven music.
London based DJ who enjoys exploring the darker, bassier corners of Jungle, Breaks, Techno and Drum & Bass, especially when it is laced with a bit of acid.

Wheel2Wheel is a Manchester based event which primarily focuses on the underground sectors to genres such as UK Garage, House, Tech House, Electro, Minimal and Breakbeat. Co-Founder Freddie SJ hosts the first hour of the show, sharing his favourites as well as recent digs across the genres, and then invites fellow friends, artists and nights from the scene to present hour-long guest mixes which aims to shine a light on their sound and who they are!


With hours of Discogs screen-time under his belt and a passion for 90's & early 00's releases, expect to hear a variety of different tunes from Labels you may have never heard of and Countries you might not expect!


Give us a follow on Instagram to hear about our upcoming events and all other things music related! @wheel2wheel.mcr

subtle.n: The Ice Box Sessions with Frigid

subtle.d: Japanese DJ from Tokyo, currently living in London.  Based on UK club music, but straddles other genres such as dancehall, reggaeton, gqom and amapiano.

Hailing from northern Italy, STANDARD is a collective of artists, DJs and producers that aims at the promotion of bass music: Garage, UK Funky, Breaks, Leftfield Bass, Leftfield Techno, Dubstep, everything in between and beyond. They focus on the Italian Bass scene, showcasing new up-and-coming artists as well as established talents from all over the peninsula.

Oddkut is a producer & DJ hailing from Balakovo City, Russia. He's part of the Russian collective "United Gang" who are a Moscow-based community of local musicians, DJ's and promoters teamed up by their genuine love & interest in UK underground music, "TAЭT VREMYA" art group and the creator of the Moscow parties "Judder".

Kishan is a DJ and Producer currently based in London. Actively involved in the music scene already, he produces and mixes a wide range of genres including UK Garage, Drum & Bass, House, Disco and Afrobeat.

dublab.d: “Dying Songs focuses on melancholic electronic music but isn’t limited to that. Sometimes it gets dark, sometimes I try to mix techno awkwardly, sometimes i get nostalgic… I like stuff that’s dreamy, ghostly, pretty and sad. I’ll try out new productions of my own, as well. I’m keeping it pretty open and we’ll see how it evolves.” – Jimmy
